description:
I had been wanting to try this place since my last trip to San Francisco. The inside is awesome, it's cool to see all those old school portraits of famous Irish people (from back in the day and today). I got to sit in front of a portrait of Oscar Wilde which was cool. I ordered a glass of Murphy's and a plate of fish & chips. My meal was delicious but if I do come back, I'm just gonna come to drink no food. Why ? Because it's too expensive ;-;

Yeah I know it's downtown San Francisco but woah, easy on my wallet there. The employees were nice so only thing that stops it from being 5 stars is the price. 

TL;DR ? : Really good but expensive.
